WEBVTT

01:40.380 --> 01:48.740
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP16]

02:06.459 --> 02:07.619
Mr. Xu, this isn't quite what we

02:07.619 --> 02:08.740
had in mind, is it?

02:11.940 --> 02:13.220
As long as there's even one person,

02:13.259 --> 02:14.660
we must serve the people well.

02:15.140 --> 02:16.620
Does one person count as "the people"?

02:17.660 --> 02:18.819
Aren't there two of them?

02:19.699 --> 02:22.139
The character for "crowd" requires at least three people, right?

02:25.900 --> 02:26.859
You two great lawyers,

02:26.859 --> 02:27.500
just now,

02:27.500 --> 02:29.500
Baoyun's wife went to the guesthouse looking for you.

02:29.819 --> 02:31.180
She said our meeting location

02:31.299 --> 02:32.419
has been changed to the neighborhood committee office.

02:32.859 --> 02:33.739
This place is too small

02:33.739 --> 02:34.780
for so many people.

02:37.100 --> 02:38.419
Not enough room here, huh?

02:39.259 --> 02:40.419
Alright, please lead the way.

02:40.419 --> 02:41.579
Alright, alright, I'll take you there.

02:41.579 --> 02:42.299
It must be...

02:42.819 --> 02:43.739
This way, there's no room for everyone.

02:43.739 --> 02:44.620
How many people are there?

02:45.460 --> 02:46.100
Mr. Xu,

02:46.100 --> 02:47.380
did we take a wrong turn again?

02:47.859 --> 02:49.060
All free, no charge.

02:49.060 --> 02:49.539
No charge.

02:49.539 --> 02:50.539
No charge, that's right.

02:51.380 --> 02:51.979
It's so lively.

02:51.979 --> 02:53.340
Is this a wedding?

02:55.419 --> 02:56.979
You did something great today.

02:57.299 --> 02:58.340
The great lawyer is here!

02:58.380 --> 02:59.900
Great lawyer, great lawyer!

03:00.019 --> 03:00.660
See?

03:02.180 --> 03:02.819
The lawyer is here.

03:02.819 --> 03:04.019
I have something to ask you.

03:06.500 --> 03:07.460
No rush, no rush.

03:08.019 --> 03:08.579
Alright, alright.

03:08.579 --> 03:09.699
Don't push, don't push, don't push.

03:11.620 --> 03:12.380
Thank you, thank you.

03:12.380 --> 03:13.579
Everyone is too kind.

03:14.340 --> 03:15.579
Don't push, don't push, don't push.

03:15.579 --> 03:16.900
Make way, make way.

03:17.100 --> 03:18.259
Make way, make way.

03:19.780 --> 03:20.579
Everyone, listen to me.

03:20.579 --> 03:21.419
Listen to me.

03:22.259 --> 03:23.180
This person

03:23.460 --> 03:26.900
is a great lawyer with a lawyer's license.

03:27.819 --> 03:29.660
Mr. Liu.

03:33.859 --> 03:35.139
I'm not done, I'm not done.

03:35.460 --> 03:36.620
They came here specifically

03:37.060 --> 03:38.060
to provide free

03:38.340 --> 03:39.500
legal consultation services

03:39.500 --> 03:41.139
to everyone, free of charge.

03:41.460 --> 03:43.579
Let's give them a warm welcome!

03:44.819 --> 03:46.699
Welcome, welcome!

03:47.060 --> 03:48.380
Th-thank you all.

03:48.380 --> 03:48.780
Everyone,

03:48.780 --> 03:50.019
there's no need to applaud for me.

03:50.019 --> 03:51.660
Actually, I, I am Mr. Xu's...

03:51.660 --> 03:53.100
You're being too modest.

03:53.100 --> 03:54.139
Come on, please come in, no...

03:54.180 --> 03:55.180
Come on, sit, sit, sit.

03:55.180 --> 03:56.579
Great Lawyer Chen, please.

03:57.340 --> 03:58.259
Please, please, please.

03:58.259 --> 03:58.979
Is this Mr. Chen?

03:58.979 --> 03:59.419
Come, come.

03:59.419 --> 04:00.139
This is Mr. Chen.

04:00.139 --> 04:00.859
He has the qualification certificate.

04:00.940 --> 04:01.539
Look.

04:01.699 --> 04:02.859
It's okay, let's begin.

04:02.859 --> 04:03.979
Everyone is very enthusiastic.

04:04.460 --> 04:05.340
Xu,

04:05.539 --> 04:07.259
there are quite a lot of people today.

04:07.660 --> 04:08.780
Make sure you do a good job as the assistant.

04:09.460 --> 04:11.060
No problem, I'll take notes for you.

04:12.419 --> 04:13.620
Everyone, don't rush.

04:13.620 --> 04:14.460
One at a time.

04:14.699 --> 04:15.819
Thank you, Mr. Xu.

04:20.019 --> 04:21.460
I go first, I go first, I go first.

04:22.220 --> 04:23.340
You go first, you go first.

04:30.859 --> 04:33.179
May I ask what legal issue you'd like to

04:33.179 --> 04:34.179
consult about?

04:35.100 --> 04:35.979
This matter,

04:35.979 --> 04:37.499
it makes me angry just talking about it.

04:38.059 --> 04:40.460
My girl just came of age this year,

04:40.859 --> 04:42.260
and that Zhao Laosi's son—

04:42.260 --> 04:43.140
he ruined her.

04:48.460 --> 04:50.299
Then may I ask,

04:50.379 --> 04:51.780
what is the relationship between your daughter and Zhao Laosi's son?

04:51.780 --> 04:52.900
your daughter and Zhao Laosi's son?

04:53.619 --> 04:54.700
What relationship could there be?

04:55.020 --> 04:55.900
They only met once.

04:56.299 --> 04:57.780
They didn't even know each other before.

05:01.059 --> 05:02.299
This is a serious problem.

05:04.939 --> 05:05.619
Auntie,

05:05.739 --> 05:06.859
did you call the police at the time?

05:07.619 --> 05:09.340
Call the police for this?

05:11.260 --> 05:12.460
Auntie, when something like this happens,

05:12.460 --> 05:14.260
you need to call the police immediately.

05:15.460 --> 05:16.580
The baby is already born.

05:17.179 --> 05:17.979
Still need to call the police?

05:18.340 --> 05:19.539
Will it help?

05:19.859 --> 05:20.979
Had a baby?

05:24.979 --> 05:26.179
Well, Auntie,

05:26.539 --> 05:27.580
would you be able to tell us

05:27.580 --> 05:28.939
the detailed course of events?

05:29.140 --> 05:30.340
Because this case

05:30.340 --> 05:31.460
is quite heinous.

05:31.660 --> 05:32.419
Is that so?

05:34.020 --> 05:35.299
I don't believe what he said.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.660
Mr. Chen, what do you think?

05:37.140 --> 05:38.059
He's right.

05:38.979 --> 05:40.419
If conditions permit,

05:40.419 --> 05:41.580
it would be best if your daughter

05:41.580 --> 05:42.739
meet with us.

05:42.859 --> 05:44.619
What's the point of having her come?

05:44.739 --> 05:45.619
Of course it's useful.

05:45.660 --> 05:46.700
By talking directly to

05:46.700 --> 05:47.780
the person involved,

05:47.780 --> 05:48.499
we can get a better

05:48.499 --> 05:49.299
understanding of the case.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.020
You mean

05:52.020 --> 05:53.100
have her come herself

05:53.100 --> 05:54.140
and tell us what happened?

05:54.499 --> 05:55.059
Yes.

05:56.780 --> 05:57.660
Such a big deal...

06:00.059 --> 06:01.260
Is there some inconvenience?

06:02.260 --> 06:03.660
Of course there's an inconvenience!

06:04.220 --> 06:05.820
She can't talk!

06:11.539 --> 06:12.780
Here she comes, here she comes.

06:18.299 --> 06:19.780
This is my girl.

06:19.780 --> 06:20.379
You...

06:20.460 --> 06:21.539
The "daughter" you mentioned...

06:21.859 --> 06:23.499
is... is this?

06:24.739 --> 06:26.059
Isn't our girl pretty?

06:28.460 --> 06:29.220
You tell me,

06:29.780 --> 06:30.660
shouldn't Zhao Laosi's son

06:30.660 --> 06:31.780
compensate us?

06:32.419 --> 06:33.260
What is this?

06:33.260 --> 06:33.859
Are you joking?

06:33.859 --> 06:34.739
Sorry, Auntie,

06:35.780 --> 06:37.460
that might be a bit difficult.

06:37.460 --> 06:38.780
Legally speaking,

06:38.979 --> 06:41.299
regarding this type of behavior between animals,

06:41.299 --> 06:42.739
there are no clear provisions.

06:42.780 --> 06:44.100
So, so our girl

06:44.100 --> 06:45.260
just got ruined for nothing?

06:47.220 --> 06:47.700
How about this, Auntie,

06:47.700 --> 06:48.820
you, you go and rest now,

06:48.820 --> 06:49.100
alright?

06:49.100 --> 06:49.859
We'll invite the next person.

06:50.539 --> 06:51.539
Excuse me, you can take a break.

06:54.340 --> 06:55.100
Comrade Lawyer,

06:57.100 --> 06:57.900
Comrade Lawyer,

06:58.379 --> 06:59.460
I have something,

06:59.460 --> 07:00.340
I'd like to ask.

07:00.580 --> 07:01.460
What is it? Please go ahead.

07:02.020 --> 07:03.179
I sell rice noodles.

07:03.700 --> 07:04.979
A couple of days ago,

07:05.539 --> 07:06.460
some... what do you call it...

07:07.460 --> 07:08.739
a food vlogger came to my place

07:09.299 --> 07:10.100
to eat rice noodles.

07:10.299 --> 07:11.499
He found a piece of iron wire in it.

07:12.260 --> 07:14.020
He insisted I pay him a thousand yuan,

07:14.379 --> 07:15.179
otherwise

07:15.619 --> 07:17.179
he'd expose my shop online.

07:17.379 --> 07:18.539
I swear on my conscience,

07:19.100 --> 07:20.179
I wash all the vegetables I buy

07:20.179 --> 07:21.260
several times.

07:21.379 --> 07:22.539
I do it so that others

07:22.539 --> 07:23.379
can eat with peace of mind.

07:26.059 --> 07:27.700
But I also know

07:28.260 --> 07:29.619
it was found in my place.

07:30.100 --> 07:31.379
So I thought, fine, I'll pay.

07:32.580 --> 07:33.859
But yesterday he came again.

07:34.660 --> 07:36.660
Yesterday he found a piece of

07:36.660 --> 07:37.419
glass.

07:37.700 --> 07:39.539
How could there be glass in rice noodles?

07:39.539 --> 07:40.780
I don't know, I tell you...

07:41.140 --> 07:41.580
Uncle,

07:41.580 --> 07:43.020
does your shop have surveillance cameras?

07:43.460 --> 07:44.140
No.

07:45.939 --> 07:47.059
No surveillance?

07:49.780 --> 07:51.460
If this is indeed extortion,

07:51.739 --> 07:53.539
this is probably not an isolated case.

07:56.939 --> 07:57.739
Right, Uncle.

07:57.739 --> 07:59.660
First check other nearby stores

07:59.660 --> 08:01.299
and ask in the business district's merchant group chat

08:01.739 --> 08:03.340
to see if anyone else has had the same issue.

08:03.859 --> 08:04.660
If so,

08:04.660 --> 08:06.179
see if other places have surveillance footage.

08:06.619 --> 08:07.379
If this happens frequently,

08:07.379 --> 08:08.859
it's most likely not a coincidence.

08:09.419 --> 08:11.140
We advise you to report it to the police.

08:13.419 --> 08:14.299
Okay, okay.

08:14.419 --> 08:15.219
Thank you, lawyer.

08:15.220 --> 08:15.979
Thank you, lawyer.

08:16.419 --> 08:17.100
You're welcome.

08:20.140 --> 08:20.979
Come on, next.

08:20.979 --> 08:21.660
N-next.

08:21.660 --> 08:22.539
Next.

08:39.140 --> 08:39.859
Thank you, Mr. Chen.

08:40.100 --> 08:41.019
You're too kind. Great work.

08:41.019 --> 08:41.499
No, no.

08:41.499 --> 08:42.220
Not at all, not at all.

08:42.220 --> 08:43.060
Thank you, Mr. Chen. Great work.

08:43.060 --> 08:43.940
No, no, no.

08:43.940 --> 08:44.420
Great work.

08:44.420 --> 08:45.259
Thank you, Mr. Chen.

08:45.259 --> 08:46.019
Goodbye, goodbye.

08:46.019 --> 08:46.739
Goodbye.

08:48.619 --> 08:49.379
Anyone else?

08:53.139 --> 08:54.019
Miss Ruan.

08:57.340 --> 08:58.340
What are you doing here?

09:02.139 --> 09:03.220
Are you done?

09:04.700 --> 09:05.379
Just finished.

09:06.820 --> 09:08.859
Would you like to...

09:09.580 --> 09:11.659
Excuse me, may I have a consultation right now?

09:15.019 --> 09:15.739
Of course.

09:15.979 --> 09:16.619
Please, have a seat.

09:17.580 --> 09:18.659
Please, sit over here.

09:24.580 --> 09:25.540
Lawyers,

09:26.139 --> 09:27.540
I've met a romantic con artist.

09:28.659 --> 09:30.060
First, don't rush.

09:30.060 --> 09:31.300
Tell us the specifics.

09:31.580 --> 09:34.019
Is the other party married but pretending to be single,

09:34.019 --> 09:35.139
or did they scam you out of money?

09:35.779 --> 09:36.580
Neither.

09:37.379 --> 09:38.979
Well, if it doesn't involve property

09:38.979 --> 09:40.060
or marital fraud,

09:40.060 --> 09:40.540
legally speaking,

09:40.540 --> 09:42.060
it might be difficult to assist you.

09:42.060 --> 09:43.859
But he deceived my feelings!

09:44.420 --> 09:44.979
He's a

09:44.979 --> 09:46.540
two-faced liar!

09:46.659 --> 09:47.580
A homebody guy

09:47.580 --> 09:48.259
pretended in front of me

09:48.259 --> 09:49.540
to be an outgoing, athletic guy,

09:49.540 --> 09:50.619
and without any psychological burden,

09:50.619 --> 09:51.619
kept up the act for three months!

09:51.779 --> 09:52.940
Isn't that too much?

09:53.460 --> 09:54.460
Isn't that awful?

09:55.580 --> 09:56.540
That's terrible!

09:58.659 --> 10:00.779
Right, it's indeed terrible.

10:04.420 --> 10:05.700
May I ask you something?

10:06.259 --> 10:07.300
During this time,

10:07.499 --> 10:08.220
did he show any signs

10:08.220 --> 10:09.460
of wanting to confess?

10:12.259 --> 10:13.420
There were a few times,

10:13.820 --> 10:15.100
but in the end, he never said it.

10:15.979 --> 10:16.859
Coward.

10:17.100 --> 10:18.060
He's just a coward.

10:19.340 --> 10:20.340
He's just a coward.

10:20.659 --> 10:21.859
You're absolutely right.

10:24.580 --> 10:25.659
But think about it this way:

10:27.460 --> 10:28.739
Over past few months,

10:29.540 --> 10:31.100
maybe he was struggling too.

10:36.060 --> 10:37.859
It's not like you said,

10:38.180 --> 10:39.659
that he had no psychological burden at all.

10:41.420 --> 10:42.060
Of course,

10:42.580 --> 10:43.940
lying is definitely wrong.

10:44.300 --> 10:45.739
I'm not trying to make excuses for him.

10:46.220 --> 10:47.619
I'm just trying to comfort you a bit.

10:48.859 --> 10:50.220
Hearing you say that

10:50.499 --> 10:51.460
does make me feel a bit better.

10:52.220 --> 10:53.580
But I still won't forgive him.

10:54.460 --> 10:56.420
Of course, that's your right.

10:57.859 --> 10:58.940
Besides that,

10:59.060 --> 11:00.100
what is your demand?

11:05.139 --> 11:07.259
I, I want him to apologize to me.

11:07.659 --> 11:08.580
Is that reasonable?

11:09.180 --> 11:09.979
Of course it's reasonable.

11:10.739 --> 11:11.619
Although in this regard,

11:11.619 --> 11:12.019
legally speaking,

11:12.019 --> 11:13.379
there is no mandatory regulation,

11:13.940 --> 11:14.820
but honesty

11:14.940 --> 11:16.060
is a moral obligation

11:16.060 --> 11:16.700
we should follow.

11:17.379 --> 11:18.139
And within

11:18.139 --> 11:19.300
this relationship of yours,

11:19.779 --> 11:20.899
he did cause you

11:20.899 --> 11:21.700
emotional distress.

11:21.899 --> 11:22.859
So you have the right

11:22.899 --> 11:24.100
to demand an apology from him.

11:24.580 --> 11:25.460
But, but he thinks

11:25.460 --> 11:26.779
it was a white lie.

11:33.420 --> 11:34.940
Whether it's a white lie

11:35.779 --> 11:36.779
is for you to decide,

11:37.180 --> 11:37.979
not him.

11:39.340 --> 11:39.940
For you,

11:39.940 --> 11:41.220
no matter what the intention

11:41.220 --> 11:41.779
behind the lie was,

11:42.300 --> 11:43.019
it doesn't change

11:43.019 --> 11:44.060
the fact that it resulted

11:44.060 --> 11:44.940
in harm to you.

11:46.499 --> 11:48.540
He has no grounds to argue otherwise.

11:52.180 --> 11:53.460
So a mistake is a mistake.

11:59.940 --> 12:01.100
You should say to her

12:02.899 --> 12:03.580
I'm sorry.

12:05.420 --> 12:06.379
[Why are you looking at me?]

12:07.700 --> 12:09.340
[He's apologizing to me.]

12:17.100 --> 12:17.899
Mr. Chen,

12:19.060 --> 12:19.940
you two go ahead.

12:19.940 --> 12:20.979
I'll head back first.

12:21.659 --> 12:22.499
Th-this, you're leaving already?

12:22.499 --> 12:23.100
Miss Ruan?

12:25.779 --> 12:26.859
Miss Ruan, goodbye!

13:14.180 --> 13:14.779
Mom.

13:14.979 --> 13:16.940
This way, this way, vertical looks good.

13:16.940 --> 13:18.100
Yu, Yu.

13:18.820 --> 13:19.379
Yu.

13:19.379 --> 13:20.060
Last time you mentioned

13:20.060 --> 13:21.019
the place for inspiration,

13:21.019 --> 13:21.899
how was it?

13:23.340 --> 13:25.379
It was great, the little courtyard was beautiful.

13:26.540 --> 13:27.659
Let me show you.

13:28.259 --> 13:29.460
Dad would definitely like it.

13:31.460 --> 13:33.340
Look, there are even fish.

13:34.619 --> 13:36.180
This courtyard is quite cozy.

13:36.580 --> 13:37.859
What do you think? Nice, right?

13:38.139 --> 13:39.139
Dad would definitely like it.

13:39.139 --> 13:39.979
You know,

13:39.979 --> 13:40.979
this courtyard really isn't bad.

13:40.979 --> 13:41.940
Suitable for retirement.

13:42.619 --> 13:43.659
There's a little stove here.

13:45.060 --> 13:46.259
I always sit around it.

13:47.499 --> 13:48.060
See?

13:53.259 --> 13:54.100
Great writer!

13:54.619 --> 13:56.859
A day apart feels like three years!

13:57.540 --> 13:58.180
Who is it?

13:58.379 --> 13:59.700
Why didn't you go to the village committee?

13:59.700 --> 14:00.979
I even went to look for you.

14:02.259 --> 14:03.379
I just got back.

14:03.739 --> 14:04.700
Were you looking for me to...

14:04.700 --> 14:05.340
Well,

14:05.340 --> 14:06.019
I have a question

14:06.019 --> 14:07.739
I'd like to ask you.

14:08.580 --> 14:09.820
Lately these days,

14:10.139 --> 14:11.739
I've found while writing music,

14:12.019 --> 14:13.499
I just can't get the rhymes right.

14:19.340 --> 14:20.580
Here, let me sing it for you,

14:20.580 --> 14:21.659
Just feel it for yourself.

14:22.139 --> 14:22.940
Shishan?

14:23.420 --> 14:23.979
What about my lyrics?

14:23.979 --> 14:25.499
I'm video calling my parents!

14:27.420 --> 14:28.739
Maybe we can talk later?

14:28.739 --> 14:30.100
Sorry, really sorry.

14:30.460 --> 14:31.739
Auntie and Uncle,

14:32.180 --> 14:32.899
Hello.

14:32.899 --> 14:33.700
Auntie and Uncle,

14:34.220 --> 14:35.820
Wishing you a happy New Year!

14:36.060 --> 14:37.659
Happy New Year, happy New Year!

14:39.540 --> 14:40.340
You go ahead then,

14:40.340 --> 14:41.100
I won't disturb you.

14:41.180 --> 14:41.779
See you later.

14:56.220 --> 14:56.820
Yu,

14:57.139 --> 14:58.100
that boy who came in just now,

14:58.100 --> 14:58.859
who is he?

14:59.859 --> 15:00.779
Is he a local?

15:00.779 --> 15:01.540
What does he do?

15:01.540 --> 15:02.540
Tell Mom.

15:02.979 --> 15:03.979
Stop asking.

15:04.700 --> 15:05.580
What decent boy

15:05.580 --> 15:07.060
would say "a day apart feels like three years"

15:07.259 --> 15:08.659
to a girl he just met?

15:08.659 --> 15:09.580
Just asking!

15:09.580 --> 15:11.139
What's wrong with asking?

15:12.580 --> 15:13.659
Alright, Mom, Dad.

15:14.180 --> 15:14.659
He's

15:14.659 --> 15:16.100
the brother of the guesthouse owner.

15:17.139 --> 15:20.060
Although his personality is a bit unique,

15:20.139 --> 15:21.100
he's a nice person.

15:21.820 --> 15:23.379
Well, he's not as good as Xu.

15:23.379 --> 15:23.859
Right.

15:24.460 --> 15:25.060
Yu,

15:25.619 --> 15:27.139
are you still on bad terms with Xu?

15:30.580 --> 15:31.979
We're not on bad terms.

15:32.739 --> 15:34.979
He and I were never really that close.

15:35.700 --> 15:36.180
Well...

15:44.499 --> 15:45.300
Mr. Xu.

15:46.139 --> 15:47.379
I've been waiting for you for a long time.

15:48.060 --> 15:49.139
I watched your legal aid session

15:49.139 --> 15:50.259
at the village committee today.

15:50.259 --> 15:51.659
I thought it was extremely professional.

15:52.619 --> 15:53.619
So I was thinking,

15:54.580 --> 15:55.420
could you

15:55.420 --> 15:56.899
help me with a lawsuit too?

15:58.180 --> 15:59.180
You have a lawsuit too?

15:59.259 --> 15:59.899
Yes.

16:00.979 --> 16:02.460
Alright, let's sit down and talk.

16:02.540 --> 16:03.659
Okay, sure.

16:03.659 --> 16:04.700
Help him take notes.

16:05.139 --> 16:05.619
Okay.

16:05.899 --> 16:06.700
Actually,

16:06.940 --> 16:08.340
it's not really a big case.

16:08.979 --> 16:10.139
I want to sue my dad.

16:11.060 --> 16:11.659
Sue your dad?

16:11.659 --> 16:12.499
Li Shishan!

16:13.060 --> 16:14.300
You're acting up again, huh?

16:14.300 --> 16:15.540
You're hitting me again, right?

16:15.540 --> 16:16.300
You're hitting me!

16:16.300 --> 16:17.979
Hitting you? Hitting you is being lenient!

16:17.979 --> 16:18.859
Don't get physical!

16:18.859 --> 16:19.979
What's wrong with having a dream?

16:20.499 --> 16:21.580
"Having a dream"?

16:21.580 --> 16:22.859
That's just daydreaming!

16:23.180 --> 16:24.540
Mr. Xu, I want to add a defendant!

16:24.540 --> 16:25.580
I want to sue my sister!

16:25.580 --> 16:27.060
Just wait till I catch you!

16:27.139 --> 16:27.779
I'll get you!

16:27.779 --> 16:30.499
If I don't daydream, how can I have a dream?

16:30.700 --> 16:31.940
What's wrong with having a dream?

16:32.499 --> 16:33.779
You can keep my ID card,

16:33.779 --> 16:34.779
but you can't keep me!

16:34.940 --> 16:36.180
Even if you could keep me,

16:36.180 --> 16:37.580
you can't keep my heart!

16:41.540 --> 16:42.379
Go and check it out.

16:42.379 --> 16:43.580
Understand the situation.

16:46.180 --> 16:47.139
Okay, okay.

16:52.139 --> 16:52.779
Go!

17:01.779 --> 17:02.460
Mr. Xu,

17:02.460 --> 17:03.820
About Li Shishan,

17:03.820 --> 17:04.540
I've figured everything out.

17:04.659 --> 17:05.499
Good, sit down.

17:06.220 --> 17:06.659
Okay.

17:07.060 --> 17:07.779
What did they say?

17:09.180 --> 17:10.060
Well,

17:10.499 --> 17:12.259
he's a fan of Li Shican, right?

17:12.379 --> 17:14.379
So he also wants to sing and become a singer.

17:14.739 --> 17:16.580
But his family doesn't agree.

17:16.940 --> 17:18.340
It seems they're afraid he'll

17:18.340 --> 17:19.139
mess around alone out there.

17:19.460 --> 17:19.940
His father

17:19.940 --> 17:21.220
even confiscated his ID card.

17:22.540 --> 17:23.100
So then,

17:23.139 --> 17:24.500
go to their house tomorrow.

17:24.740 --> 17:25.580
Focus on mediation.

17:25.899 --> 17:26.500
No problem.

17:30.899 --> 17:31.939
You've been busy all day.

17:32.060 --> 17:32.780
Hungry?

17:33.340 --> 17:34.580
Yeah, a little.

17:35.139 --> 17:36.659
She must be hungry too, right?

17:36.899 --> 17:37.580
What did you say?

17:38.859 --> 17:39.379
Nothing.

17:40.060 --> 17:40.500
By the way,

17:40.899 --> 17:41.500
when you came back,

17:41.500 --> 17:42.619
did you see Miss Ruan?

17:42.939 --> 17:43.699
I did.

17:43.899 --> 17:45.859
She's in the kitchen with Cai,

17:45.859 --> 17:46.780
getting hotpot ready.

17:48.619 --> 17:49.820
Smells amazing, Mr. Xu.

17:50.100 --> 17:50.580
But,

17:50.580 --> 17:51.580
we should prepare

17:51.580 --> 17:52.379
our own dinner first.

17:52.500 --> 17:53.540
I'm so hungry right now.

17:55.580 --> 17:57.540
They're preparing dinner in the kitchen,

17:57.780 --> 17:58.699
making hotpot.

18:01.060 --> 18:02.060
Didn't they invite us?

18:03.580 --> 18:05.260
Cai did invite me when she saw me,

18:05.260 --> 18:05.980
but I said

18:05.980 --> 18:07.340
we had other plans.

18:08.419 --> 18:09.419
I figured it wouldn't be right

18:09.419 --> 18:10.580
to keep freeloading meals.

18:10.780 --> 18:11.659
This doesn't align with

18:11.659 --> 18:12.300
the legal aid principle of

18:12.300 --> 18:13.659
"not taking a single thing from the masses."

18:14.580 --> 18:15.580
You're right.

18:15.780 --> 18:17.179
But what do you mean by "freeloading"?

18:20.659 --> 18:21.139
We should

18:21.139 --> 18:22.780
be a little more flexible.

18:23.459 --> 18:24.100
Think of it this way:

18:25.780 --> 18:28.179
we could pay,

18:28.500 --> 18:29.699
or we could

18:29.699 --> 18:30.899
earn it through our own efforts,

18:31.300 --> 18:32.300
helping them out,

18:32.859 --> 18:34.179
using our own labor

18:34.459 --> 18:35.459
to exchange for food.

18:36.980 --> 18:37.540
Alright.

18:37.659 --> 18:38.939
Then let's go and work right away.

18:38.939 --> 18:39.899
But, Mr. Xu,

18:39.899 --> 18:41.179
if they've already finished cooking,

18:41.179 --> 18:42.419
what exactly can we do?

18:45.300 --> 18:46.300
Do you eat cilantro?

18:46.300 --> 18:47.020
I eat everything.

18:47.179 --> 18:47.899
Great!

18:47.899 --> 18:48.659
I'll put in some extra for you.

18:49.780 --> 18:50.459
You eat scallions too, right?

18:50.459 --> 18:50.859
Yes.

18:50.859 --> 18:51.500
Good.

18:51.500 --> 18:52.740
I like people who aren't picky eaters.

18:54.540 --> 18:55.500
A little more scallion for you.

18:56.540 --> 18:57.300
Cai!

18:57.300 --> 18:58.740
Um, that, that Mr. Xu,

18:58.740 --> 19:00.139
he, his stomach is upset.

19:00.139 --> 19:01.179
Do you have any stomach medicine?

19:02.419 --> 19:03.300
Stomach upset?

19:03.379 --> 19:04.139
Why

19:04.139 --> 19:05.300
so suddenly?

19:05.939 --> 19:06.500
Yes, yes.

19:06.500 --> 19:07.780
Under the bedside table,

19:07.780 --> 19:08.580
there's a first aid kit,

19:08.580 --> 19:09.859
with some regular medicine inside.

19:10.459 --> 19:11.500
Is it serious?

19:11.619 --> 19:14.340
He, he sh-should just be...

19:14.340 --> 19:15.699
Is it cramping or...?

19:15.699 --> 19:16.379
It's not foot pain,

19:16.379 --> 19:17.740
it's stomach pain, Cai!

19:17.740 --> 19:18.580
I know it's stomach!

19:18.580 --> 19:20.899
I meant, is it cramping or burning,

19:20.939 --> 19:21.980
or, that...

19:22.500 --> 19:23.699
Chen Hui, I've found it.

19:24.100 --> 19:25.179
Under that bedside table,

19:25.179 --> 19:26.100
I've already taken the medicine.

19:26.100 --> 19:26.659
How is it?

19:27.459 --> 19:28.139
Not bad.

19:28.139 --> 19:30.219
It's probably just from irregular habits,

19:30.780 --> 19:31.580
got too hungry.

19:33.619 --> 19:35.020
From hunger, huh?

19:35.260 --> 19:36.459
Quick, quick, quick.

19:36.580 --> 19:38.060
There's this big table full of food,

19:38.060 --> 19:39.060
we can't finish it all.

19:39.060 --> 19:39.699
Come on, join us.

19:39.699 --> 19:40.939
Alright, that's too kind.

19:41.500 --> 19:42.379
Actually, no.

19:43.100 --> 19:44.179
You have a stomach ache,

19:44.179 --> 19:45.260
you shouldn't eat hotpot.

19:46.260 --> 19:47.939
Cai, don't worry.

19:48.300 --> 19:49.740
For someone as capable as Mr. Xu,

19:50.060 --> 19:50.980
hotpot is nothing—

19:51.179 --> 19:52.179
he could even eat a pot of boiling oil.

19:53.899 --> 19:54.379
Right.

19:54.379 --> 19:54.980
Alright.

19:55.060 --> 19:56.540
And I just made it spicy,

19:56.540 --> 19:58.020
it warms the stomach. It's fine.

19:58.100 --> 19:58.859
Eat, eat.

19:58.859 --> 19:59.899
I'll go get you some bowls and plates.

19:59.899 --> 20:00.820
Thank you, Cai, thank you.

20:00.820 --> 20:01.459
Sorry for the trouble, Cai.

20:03.219 --> 20:03.740
Miss Ruan,

20:03.740 --> 20:04.740
I heard today's ingredients

20:04.740 --> 20:05.340
were all bought by you.

20:05.340 --> 20:06.219
Um, well,

20:06.219 --> 20:08.580
we'll give you the meal money tomorrow.

20:08.699 --> 20:10.179
Don't be so polite, it's fine.

20:10.500 --> 20:11.379
No, we must.

20:11.379 --> 20:12.139
This isn't polite,

20:12.740 --> 20:13.459
can't we just

20:13.459 --> 20:15.379
treat you back tomorrow instead?

20:18.820 --> 20:19.740
Right, right. Miss Ruan, um,

20:19.740 --> 20:20.939
we'll treat you tomorrow.

20:21.020 --> 20:21.580
It's okay.

20:21.980 --> 20:23.139
Look what this is.

20:23.899 --> 20:26.060
I learned to make apple cider from someone.

20:26.060 --> 20:27.300
You guys try it for me.

20:27.300 --> 20:28.219
Apple cider?

20:29.500 --> 20:31.580
The alcohol content isn't high.

20:31.580 --> 20:33.060
You can drink as much as you like.

20:34.020 --> 20:34.859
You can't drink.

20:34.980 --> 20:35.939
You just took medicine,

20:35.939 --> 20:36.820
you can't drink alcohol.

20:37.580 --> 20:38.899
A little bit shouldn't matter.

20:40.619 --> 20:41.459
Sis, it's fine.

20:41.699 --> 20:43.500
Mr. Xu knows his limits.

20:44.300 --> 20:44.899
Alright.

20:45.219 --> 20:46.540
The alcohol content isn't high.

20:47.419 --> 20:48.179
Just a little, okay?

20:48.540 --> 20:49.179
Got it.

20:50.260 --> 20:50.780
Here.

20:51.500 --> 20:52.260
Thanks.

20:52.260 --> 20:53.939
How is it? Good?

20:54.060 --> 20:55.580
It's very good, very fragrant, Sis.

20:56.020 --> 20:56.859
Wonderful!

20:57.260 --> 20:58.980
Drink up, there's plenty.

20:59.260 --> 21:00.340
The fruit flavor is quite strong.

21:00.340 --> 21:00.980
Right?

21:01.699 --> 21:03.100
No matter how much you drink this, you won't get drunk.

21:04.100 --> 21:05.659
So you don't need to worry.

21:06.580 --> 21:08.100
Perfect for cutting the grease from the hotpot.

21:10.379 --> 21:11.340
I'll do it myself, I'll do it myself.

21:14.780 --> 21:15.459
Thanks.

21:16.459 --> 21:17.260
So fragrant.

21:17.260 --> 21:17.939
Really?

21:19.179 --> 21:20.060
Quick, taste it.

21:24.500 --> 21:25.459
That's enough.

21:25.459 --> 21:25.980
Too much.

21:27.740 --> 21:28.260
See?

21:28.260 --> 21:28.939
What's wrong?

21:29.459 --> 21:31.020
The wind's making me a bit dizzy.

21:31.659 --> 21:32.419
Mr. Chen,

21:32.419 --> 21:34.300
I think your tolerance is still not great.

21:34.379 --> 21:36.419
I don't feel anything after drinking it.

21:37.740 --> 21:38.419
You said...

21:38.459 --> 21:39.419
Come on, Miss Ruan.

21:40.300 --> 21:41.100
Now this isn't right.

21:41.100 --> 21:42.219
I have to be polite,

21:42.219 --> 21:42.740
you know?

21:42.939 --> 21:43.419
Come on.

21:43.419 --> 21:44.300
No, no, no.

21:44.300 --> 21:45.659
Chen.

21:45.659 --> 21:46.899
Come on, let me help you up.

21:46.899 --> 21:47.580
I'll take you back first.

21:47.740 --> 21:48.899
Come on, come on, let me help you up.

21:48.899 --> 21:49.859
Okay, I am a bit dizzy.

21:49.859 --> 21:51.179
I, I'll go back first.

21:51.179 --> 21:51.780
Miss Ruan,

21:51.780 --> 21:53.540
you don't need to help me.

21:53.540 --> 21:54.260
I can go back by myself.

21:54.260 --> 21:54.820
No helping, no helping.

21:54.820 --> 21:55.980
Mr. Xu, you enjoy your meal.

21:55.980 --> 21:56.780
I'll go back now.

21:56.780 --> 21:57.859
Cai, I'm going back.

21:57.859 --> 21:58.659
I don't need...

21:58.659 --> 21:59.859
I don't need anyone to help me.

21:59.859 --> 22:01.060
Watch your step.

22:01.659 --> 22:02.619
Take your time eating, Mr. Xu.

22:02.619 --> 22:03.659
Go on, go.

22:09.139 --> 22:10.260
Then I'll walk you back too.

22:16.060 --> 22:16.699
Ruan Yu.

22:19.060 --> 22:19.780
Are you okay?

22:21.459 --> 22:22.060
I'm fine.

22:24.980 --> 22:26.300
I thought you had left.

22:28.619 --> 22:29.260
Leave?

22:30.899 --> 22:32.740
Where could I go?

22:33.980 --> 22:35.659
I've already hidden myself here,

22:36.540 --> 22:38.740
and he still caught me.

22:41.020 --> 22:42.580
Then if I hide in a cave,

22:44.139 --> 22:46.859
he shouldn't be able to find me, right?

22:48.980 --> 22:49.859
You're drunk.

22:50.379 --> 22:51.459
Let me take you back to your room first.

22:52.139 --> 22:52.619
No.

22:54.020 --> 22:54.859
I'm not going back.

22:55.980 --> 22:57.219
I want to stay here

22:57.459 --> 22:58.740
and be a caveman.

22:59.780 --> 23:00.459
That way,

23:01.939 --> 23:03.020
that way, Xu Huaisong

23:03.780 --> 23:04.780
won't be able to find me.

23:23.260 --> 23:24.459
Then may I ask,

23:26.859 --> 23:27.699
why are you afraid

23:27.699 --> 23:28.780
of encountering Xu Huaisong?

23:33.659 --> 23:34.459
Because...

23:36.300 --> 23:39.020
because it's just too embarrassing.

23:40.980 --> 23:42.500
In front of him,

23:43.340 --> 23:45.379
I was so confident,

23:46.580 --> 23:48.899
put on an act for so long.

23:50.100 --> 23:51.139
I didn't expect

23:52.780 --> 23:54.300
that he saw through me

23:54.300 --> 23:56.379
from the very beginning.

23:58.260 --> 24:00.419
And in my novel,

24:01.459 --> 24:03.300
I even said he liked me.

24:06.100 --> 24:07.500
He must think

24:08.459 --> 24:10.500
think I'm a fool.

24:17.260 --> 24:18.500
I can promise you,

24:19.780 --> 24:20.500
Xu Huaisong

24:20.500 --> 24:22.139
never thought of you that way.

24:24.060 --> 24:25.300
Not only did he not think that,

24:27.939 --> 24:29.459
he actually thought you were adorable.

24:32.139 --> 24:33.219
And he's very grateful

24:34.419 --> 24:35.699
that you liked him back then.

24:37.300 --> 24:38.820
Wouldn't he think

24:40.740 --> 24:42.580
that turning an unrequited crush

24:43.939 --> 24:46.060
into mutual feelings

24:48.139 --> 24:50.659
is something ridiculous?

24:54.060 --> 24:55.060
Of course not.

24:56.980 --> 24:58.100
Mutual feelings,

25:00.060 --> 25:01.379
when you liked him,

25:01.899 --> 25:03.179
he liked you too.

25:04.699 --> 25:05.899
Isn't that a

25:05.899 --> 25:07.260
particularly beautiful thing?

25:10.980 --> 25:11.740
Besides,

25:15.459 --> 25:18.859
who said you adapted it?

26:57.260 --> 26:58.020
Are you okay?

26:59.379 --> 27:00.179
No, I'm fine.

27:09.580 --> 27:12.340
Because it's just too embarrassing.

27:13.780 --> 27:15.379
In front of him,

27:16.139 --> 27:18.179
I was so confident,

27:19.379 --> 27:21.619
put on an act for so long.

27:22.899 --> 27:23.980
I didn't expect

27:25.659 --> 27:27.100
that he saw through me

27:27.100 --> 27:29.340
from the very beginning.

27:33.899 --> 27:36.179
And in my novel,

27:36.740 --> 27:38.619
I even said he liked me.

27:41.419 --> 27:42.659
He must think

27:43.740 --> 27:45.780
think I'm a fool.

27:51.340 --> 27:52.659
I told him everything.

28:11.100 --> 28:12.260
I can promise you,

28:13.659 --> 28:14.379
Xu Huaisong

28:14.379 --> 28:15.899
never thought that way.

28:17.939 --> 28:19.179
Not only did he not think that,

28:21.780 --> 28:23.340
he actually thought you were adorable.

28:25.980 --> 28:27.100
And he's very grateful

28:28.379 --> 28:29.619
that you liked him so much back then.

28:36.859 --> 28:38.260
Still so embarrassing.

28:39.780 --> 28:40.859
I'll do some reconnaissance first.

28:41.580 --> 28:42.859
You go out for breakfast

28:42.859 --> 28:44.060
like you're sneaking around.

28:44.060 --> 28:44.780
You just

28:44.780 --> 28:46.020
spoke some truth after drinking.

28:47.300 --> 28:48.139
I'm just afraid

28:48.780 --> 28:50.300
there's something even more shocking.

28:51.179 --> 28:52.300
For someone who blacked out,

28:52.300 --> 28:53.580
you know how to get straight to the point,

28:53.659 --> 28:55.179
only remembering that someone said you were adorable,

28:55.179 --> 28:56.060
huh?

29:00.780 --> 29:02.139
Stop teasing me.

29:03.379 --> 29:03.939
I

29:04.780 --> 29:05.859
I have a feeling

29:06.100 --> 29:06.659
that later on,

29:06.659 --> 29:08.020
he seemed to have said something else.

29:08.340 --> 29:09.179
But no matter how I think,

29:09.179 --> 29:10.340
I can't remember.

29:11.340 --> 29:12.980
Then ask him to help you remember.

29:12.980 --> 29:13.699
Just ask him.

29:16.300 --> 29:17.219
Better not.

29:18.179 --> 29:20.699
Don't they say the worst thing is

29:21.379 --> 29:22.580
someone helping you remember after you're drunk?

29:23.500 --> 29:24.379
How about...

29:25.500 --> 29:27.459
If he doesn't ask, I won't say.

29:28.500 --> 29:29.219
If he asks,

29:30.300 --> 29:31.100
I'll act surprised.

29:34.179 --> 29:35.340
"Oh, that happened?"

29:35.899 --> 29:37.139
"Did I drink that much?"

29:37.699 --> 29:38.540
No way, Miss Ruan.

29:38.540 --> 29:40.419
You were laughing at my low tolerance last night.

29:40.740 --> 29:42.260
You're more drunk than I was!

29:45.980 --> 29:46.939
Here, drink some honey water.

29:49.139 --> 29:50.179
It helps sober you up and soothes the stomach.

29:51.580 --> 29:52.219
Thanks.

30:07.699 --> 30:09.020
About last night,

30:10.300 --> 30:11.459
I don't remember anything.

30:13.980 --> 30:15.659
Did something happen yesterday

30:15.939 --> 30:17.260
that I should remember?

30:22.219 --> 30:23.899
Who said you adapted it?

30:31.139 --> 30:31.859
I was planning

30:31.859 --> 30:32.980
to tell you a story.

30:33.060 --> 30:33.980
What story?

30:34.580 --> 30:35.379
And then?

30:35.540 --> 30:36.340
And then...

30:38.179 --> 30:39.419
I overestimated a writer's

30:39.419 --> 30:40.780
ability to understand when drunk.

30:44.540 --> 30:44.939
Morning.

30:44.939 --> 30:45.780
Morning, Cai.

30:45.780 --> 30:46.899
Everyone's up?

30:48.139 --> 30:49.020
Young people

30:49.219 --> 30:50.379
have great energy, huh?

30:50.740 --> 30:51.540
Hungover from last night,

30:51.540 --> 30:52.780
and still able to get up this early.

30:53.179 --> 30:54.820
We almost didn't make it, Cai.

30:54.820 --> 30:56.699
Your apple cider is too strong.

30:57.340 --> 30:58.020
Really?

30:58.899 --> 31:00.139
Then I'll have to improve it.

31:00.859 --> 31:01.459
By the way,

31:01.459 --> 31:02.740
you were busy all day yesterday.

31:02.740 --> 31:04.179
What are you all planning to do today?

31:05.540 --> 31:07.580
I heard the intangible cultural heritage workshop in town

31:07.580 --> 31:08.379
is quite interesting.

31:08.379 --> 31:09.859
I plan to go check it out later.

31:11.060 --> 31:11.859
What about you, Mr. Xu?

31:12.939 --> 31:14.459
We don't have any work arrangements.

31:14.580 --> 31:15.540
Let's go together then.

31:15.820 --> 31:17.340
Mr. Xu, aren't you supposed to...

31:17.340 --> 31:18.100
I thought about it,

31:18.100 --> 31:19.379
we should probably learn more about

31:19.379 --> 31:20.659
the local customs and culture

31:20.659 --> 31:21.340
so that later

31:21.340 --> 31:22.500
we can serve everyone better.

31:23.060 --> 31:24.020
That's perfect!

31:24.379 --> 31:25.780
I happen to have two

31:25.859 --> 31:27.340
experience vouchers for gourd pyrography.

31:27.540 --> 31:28.580
You two can use them for a date.

31:31.699 --> 31:32.540
Eat slowly.

31:50.379 --> 31:51.100
This is it.

31:52.419 --> 31:52.980
Let's go.

32:04.580 --> 32:05.780
No photos allowed.

32:06.020 --> 32:06.619
See?

32:08.980 --> 32:09.580
Sorry about that.

32:09.580 --> 32:10.379
We won't take any.

32:20.699 --> 32:22.219
And no interviews.

32:23.780 --> 32:24.580
No interviews.

32:32.139 --> 32:32.820
Master.

32:33.459 --> 32:35.540
We happen to have two experience vouchers.

32:35.859 --> 32:37.179
Can we make our own gourds?

32:41.219 --> 32:41.899
Sure.

32:43.260 --> 32:45.179
You pick two gourds.

32:47.980 --> 32:48.500
Okay.

32:49.020 --> 32:50.540
If you have an art background,

32:50.740 --> 32:52.459
draw directly on the gourd.

32:53.939 --> 32:55.340
If you don't,

32:56.219 --> 32:58.060
draw on the tracing paper.

32:59.740 --> 33:00.899
If you don't have the skills,

33:00.899 --> 33:02.459
don't take on the job.

33:02.859 --> 33:04.139
If you ruin a gourd,

33:04.139 --> 33:05.540
you have to buy it.

33:09.419 --> 33:10.020
Here.

33:18.659 --> 33:19.699
Thought about what to draw yet?

33:28.020 --> 33:29.699
Not sure what to trace yet.

33:31.859 --> 33:32.459
Master,

33:32.459 --> 33:33.740
do you have any good suggestions?

33:34.540 --> 33:36.060
Most young people who come here

33:37.100 --> 33:39.820
usually write some auspicious words,

33:40.379 --> 33:42.260
or draw something like a small animal.

33:43.980 --> 33:44.980
Small animal.

33:53.100 --> 33:54.740
I've got an idea.

34:05.100 --> 34:06.580
Why are you copying their idea?

34:07.419 --> 34:08.260
Think of your own.

34:09.179 --> 34:09.780
Okay.

35:15.299 --> 35:16.580
You had time to come out today,

35:17.060 --> 35:18.100
does that mean the cases you're handling

35:18.100 --> 35:18.779
are finished?

35:21.139 --> 35:22.339
I worked late last night giving preliminary legal opinions

35:22.339 --> 35:23.540
on the various cases.

35:24.139 --> 35:24.940
Today,

35:25.139 --> 35:26.179
Chen will organize them into

35:26.179 --> 35:27.380
specific legal opinion documents.

35:30.179 --> 35:31.339
So what about Li Shishan's case?

35:31.339 --> 35:31.980
How's it going?

35:32.460 --> 35:33.179
Shishan,

35:34.460 --> 35:35.100
he still insists

35:35.100 --> 35:36.100
on going to court with his father

35:36.100 --> 35:37.259
to get his ID card back.

35:42.500 --> 35:43.779
Can you file a lawsuit for that?

35:44.460 --> 35:45.980
Theoretically, it's absolutely possible.

35:46.259 --> 35:48.500
So, do you think he should litigate?

35:49.860 --> 35:51.460
If Shishan insists on it,

35:51.980 --> 35:52.860
I will still respect

35:52.860 --> 35:54.060
my client's opinion.

35:56.819 --> 35:57.659
And what about the opinion

35:57.659 --> 35:58.900
of the other party, his father?

36:00.100 --> 36:00.699
Old sir.

36:01.219 --> 36:02.940
I am Li Shishan's father!

36:03.020 --> 36:03.580
Calm down.

36:03.580 --> 36:04.139
Old sir,

36:04.420 --> 36:04.980
please calm down first.

36:04.980 --> 36:06.699
You dare encourage a son to sue his father?

36:07.100 --> 36:08.020
What's wrong with that?

36:09.100 --> 36:10.540
Old sir, please calm down.

36:10.540 --> 36:10.860
Dad!

36:10.860 --> 36:11.860
Please calm down, old sir.

36:12.460 --> 36:13.139
Please calm down.

36:13.139 --> 36:13.540
Get out!

36:13.540 --> 36:13.940
Old sir,

36:13.940 --> 36:14.420
Go!

36:14.819 --> 36:15.100
Go!

36:15.100 --> 36:16.020
Everyone out!

36:39.900 --> 36:40.619
Almost done.

36:56.900 --> 36:57.739
Let's go back.

36:58.860 --> 36:59.380
Okay.

37:01.460 --> 37:02.259
It seems...

37:05.900 --> 37:06.860
We're going the wrong way.

37:24.380 --> 37:25.500
Mr. Xu.

37:25.500 --> 37:26.940
Great writer Ruan.

37:26.940 --> 37:28.580
You two came back together?

37:28.659 --> 37:29.659
Why did you

37:29.659 --> 37:30.980
come back together?

37:32.779 --> 37:33.580
Because

37:34.380 --> 37:35.739
we went out together.

37:35.739 --> 37:36.460
Profound.

37:36.900 --> 37:38.259
Actually, I've been waiting for you all along.

37:38.779 --> 37:39.420
Mr. Xu,

37:39.739 --> 37:40.500
can we schedule a date for our case

37:40.500 --> 37:42.259
to begin?

37:43.860 --> 37:44.339
Or perhaps,

37:44.339 --> 37:45.540
you could talk with my father

37:45.540 --> 37:46.420
first?

37:46.860 --> 37:47.739
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

37:48.500 --> 37:50.819
My father has a rather strange personality,

37:51.179 --> 37:52.420
so you need to be careful.

37:53.219 --> 37:54.060
Thanks for the heads-up.

37:54.179 --> 37:55.139
We already know.

37:56.219 --> 37:57.139
What are you doing here?

37:57.980 --> 37:59.860
Mr. Xu, this is my dad.

37:59.860 --> 38:00.659
See?

38:00.659 --> 38:01.500
This is how he treats me!

38:01.500 --> 38:03.299
Take a picture, keep the evidence!

38:03.980 --> 38:05.460
Now I know Cai inherited it from whom .

38:05.500 --> 38:06.339
Stand right there!

38:06.339 --> 38:08.540
Are you going to handle this or not?

38:10.659 --> 38:11.779
I remember you said

38:11.779 --> 38:12.540
in this kind of situation,

38:12.540 --> 38:13.739
we could find someone

38:14.900 --> 38:16.299
to meddle with us.

38:20.420 --> 38:21.179
I'm leaving!

38:21.580 --> 38:22.500
I'm running away from home!

38:24.940 --> 38:26.460
Mr. Xu, see,

38:26.460 --> 38:27.980
the situation is what it is.

38:27.980 --> 38:29.139
You've seen it all.

38:29.380 --> 38:30.179
This, this lawsuit,

38:30.179 --> 38:31.299
it's not that I insist on it,

38:31.779 --> 38:33.500
it's that there's no possibility for mediation.

38:34.259 --> 38:34.940
If you insist

38:34.940 --> 38:36.060
on going to court,

38:36.339 --> 38:37.580
I respect your choice.

38:38.139 --> 38:39.659
But whether it's in court

38:39.980 --> 38:41.020
or through private mediation,

38:41.259 --> 38:41.980
these are just

38:41.980 --> 38:43.500
ways to achieve your goal.

38:43.980 --> 38:45.339
So you should think carefully

38:45.779 --> 38:47.339
about what your true goal is.

38:49.659 --> 38:50.619
Looks like you didn't catch that.

38:51.060 --> 38:51.619
Here,

38:51.619 --> 38:53.060
let me ask you in a different way.

38:53.980 --> 38:55.580
After you get your ID card,

38:55.980 --> 38:57.060
what do you plan to do?

38:57.179 --> 38:58.739
Buy a ticket and leave here!

38:58.980 --> 38:59.580
Go where?

38:59.580 --> 39:00.659
To the distance!

39:00.659 --> 39:01.699
What will you do there?

39:01.699 --> 39:03.540
Realize my musical dream!

39:03.699 --> 39:04.659
Dream?

39:05.420 --> 39:07.139
That brat,

39:07.139 --> 39:08.900
idling around all day,

39:09.420 --> 39:11.179
working sporadically,

39:11.500 --> 39:13.860
one moment it's wandering,

39:13.980 --> 39:15.420
the next it's the distance.

39:16.540 --> 39:17.900
How long can he keep it up?

39:19.460 --> 39:20.500
I don't support it.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.500
But listening just now,

39:23.980 --> 39:24.779
I feel you don't actually

39:24.779 --> 39:26.060
not support his dream.

39:26.380 --> 39:27.259
You're just afraid he

39:27.259 --> 39:29.259
might lose interest quickly and not persevere,

39:29.380 --> 39:29.900
right?

39:30.940 --> 39:31.619
That's not it.

39:32.139 --> 39:33.299
I don't support him

39:33.619 --> 39:35.420
thinking that because he can strum a guitar

39:35.699 --> 39:36.860
and hum a few songs,

39:37.179 --> 39:38.739
then he can succeed.

39:39.739 --> 39:41.259
We're just ordinary folks.

39:41.380 --> 39:42.659
How can we afford to chase

39:42.659 --> 39:43.980
something that's like

39:43.980 --> 39:45.500
a million soldiers crossing a single log bridge?

39:46.020 --> 39:46.580
No.

39:47.100 --> 39:47.739
Then how do you plan

39:47.739 --> 39:49.100
to realize your dream?

39:49.299 --> 39:49.779
Well...

39:50.900 --> 39:53.179
Once I get there,

39:53.179 --> 39:55.380
I think there will naturally be a way.

39:56.299 --> 39:57.779
Alright, so then,

39:58.259 --> 39:59.500
let me help you calculate

40:00.020 --> 40:01.259
the cost of your "distance."

40:01.259 --> 40:01.779
Okay.

40:01.779 --> 40:02.619
Let's take Mr. Chen

40:02.619 --> 40:03.500
as an example.

40:04.259 --> 40:05.540
In Hangzhou,

40:05.540 --> 40:06.580
his monthly rent

40:06.580 --> 40:07.860
is two thousand eight hundred yuan.

40:08.179 --> 40:09.779
And that's sharing with someone.

40:11.380 --> 40:12.940
His daily food expenses are about

40:13.259 --> 40:14.139
thirty to forty yuan.

40:14.339 --> 40:15.420
And that's with the subsidy

40:15.420 --> 40:16.339
from our firm.

40:16.699 --> 40:18.060
Without the subsidy,

40:18.380 --> 40:19.619
just casually ordering takeout

40:19.619 --> 40:20.500
or eating out,

40:20.739 --> 40:21.980
the monthly food cost

40:21.980 --> 40:23.380
would exceed two thousand yuan.

40:23.580 --> 40:26.179
On top of that, there are utilities,

40:26.540 --> 40:28.219
transportation, and communication costs.

40:30.380 --> 40:30.980
When you're away from home,

40:30.980 --> 40:31.980
you don't have health insurance.

40:32.100 --> 40:33.060
If you get sick,

40:33.420 --> 40:34.659
you'll have medical expenses.

40:35.860 --> 40:37.619
If you can't even eat well,

40:37.900 --> 40:38.980
or can't afford to get sick,

40:39.580 --> 40:40.500
how can you realize

40:40.500 --> 40:41.940
your own musical dream?

40:43.100 --> 40:44.380
Actually, dreaming is easy,

40:44.980 --> 40:46.580
but realizing a dream is hard.

40:48.659 --> 40:49.540
So,

40:50.219 --> 40:51.339
are you mentally prepared

40:51.779 --> 40:52.980
and financially prepared?

40:53.580 --> 40:54.779
What preparation does he have?

40:54.980 --> 40:56.619
He lacks both talent and effort.

40:57.179 --> 40:58.580
I am planning for my son.

40:58.699 --> 40:59.420
I'm not wrong.

41:01.179 --> 41:02.380
Of course, you're not wrong.

41:03.980 --> 41:06.699
I also understand that "parents' love for their child

41:06.940 --> 41:08.219
plans far ahead."

41:09.179 --> 41:10.060
Your intentions

41:10.060 --> 41:11.339
are certainly for his good.

41:11.980 --> 41:13.179
But I also think,

41:13.779 --> 41:15.100
you have your reasons,

41:15.339 --> 41:16.299
and Li Shishan

41:16.540 --> 41:17.940
has his own reasons too.

41:19.179 --> 41:19.940
Don't you think

41:20.460 --> 41:21.339
we could perhaps

41:21.339 --> 41:22.179
put ourselves in each other's shoes

41:22.699 --> 41:24.339
to reach a better consensus?

41:24.779 --> 41:25.900
What reasons does he have?

41:25.900 --> 41:27.060
You tell me.

41:29.580 --> 41:31.020
Actually, Shishan's situation

41:31.900 --> 41:32.940
reminds me

41:33.299 --> 41:34.020
of when I first

41:34.020 --> 41:35.219
decided to write novels.

41:35.980 --> 41:36.699
Back then,

41:36.699 --> 41:38.540
my parents didn't support it either.

41:38.860 --> 41:40.819
They thought it was hard to succeed,

41:40.940 --> 41:41.739
unstable.

41:42.860 --> 41:43.900
But I still

41:44.100 --> 41:46.259
stuck with it stubbornly.

41:46.380 --> 41:47.380
I thought at the time,

41:47.860 --> 41:49.020
at worst I'll hit a dead end,

41:49.139 --> 41:50.020
but at least I tried,

41:50.020 --> 41:50.980
and I wouldn't regret it.

41:51.540 --> 41:52.619
As it turned out, unexpectedly,

41:52.980 --> 41:54.619
I've kept writing until now.

41:55.420 --> 41:56.580
And now,

41:56.580 --> 41:57.060
I've also found

41:57.060 --> 41:57.900
more of this profession's

41:57.900 --> 41:58.860
value and meaning.

42:00.020 --> 42:02.259
When I see the words I've written

42:02.540 --> 42:03.699
can bring

42:03.699 --> 42:05.219
positive energy to people,

42:05.219 --> 42:06.500
I'm truly very grateful

42:06.500 --> 42:07.060
that I made the decision back then,

42:07.060 --> 42:08.139
regardless of the consequences.

42:13.179 --> 42:14.540
Actually, we, as children,

42:15.299 --> 42:16.540
are very grateful for our parents' guidance

42:16.540 --> 42:17.339
and direction.

42:18.259 --> 42:19.179
But I think

42:19.380 --> 42:20.699
this guidance and direction

42:21.420 --> 42:23.179
is meant to help us make decisions,

42:23.299 --> 42:24.139
not to make decisions

42:24.139 --> 42:25.100
for us.

42:25.299 --> 42:26.100
So I think,

42:26.980 --> 42:28.980
Shishan's reasoning might be

42:29.659 --> 42:30.619
that everyone

42:30.619 --> 42:31.299
has the right to choose

42:31.299 --> 42:32.980
their own path in life.

42:33.299 --> 42:34.500
And only by choosing for oneself

42:34.699 --> 42:35.699
and bearing the consequences,

42:36.299 --> 42:37.699
can one make this journey worthwhile.

42:39.779 --> 42:40.219
Anyway,

42:40.219 --> 42:41.940
I'm definitely going anyway.

42:42.060 --> 42:43.699
I think preparing from now on

42:44.020 --> 42:44.980
isn't too late.

42:45.779 --> 42:46.580
Mr. Xu,

42:47.540 --> 42:48.420
just help me get

42:48.420 --> 42:49.460
my ID card back,

42:49.980 --> 42:50.699
okay?

42:52.860 --> 42:54.139
I believe you're well aware

42:54.659 --> 42:56.339
that reporting the ID card lost and getting a replacement

42:56.339 --> 42:57.460
would be much faster

42:57.460 --> 42:58.380
than going to court.

42:59.980 --> 43:01.779
So what you really want, is it the ID card,

43:02.380 --> 43:04.179
or is it your family's support?

43:11.139 --> 43:11.819
Shishan,

43:12.980 --> 43:14.100
if you don't even have the courage

43:14.100 --> 43:15.779
to face your father,

43:16.420 --> 43:17.299
how can you make

43:17.299 --> 43:18.580
your father believe

43:18.739 --> 43:20.580
that you have the courage to face

43:21.060 --> 43:22.580
the unforeseen difficulties in the future?

43:30.659 --> 43:31.580
I understand.

43:32.380 --> 43:33.259
Mr. Xu.

43:40.819 --> 43:41.860
[Getting along with others]

43:42.179 --> 43:43.540
[requires remembering to put oneself in the other's shoes.]

43:44.380 --> 43:45.179
[Sometimes,]

43:45.659 --> 43:46.779
[what one thinks is care]

43:47.540 --> 43:49.100
[might be seen by the other as control.]

43:50.900 --> 43:52.020
[What one thinks is chasing a dream]

43:52.619 --> 43:54.259
[might be seen by the other as nonsense.]

43:55.500 --> 43:56.659
[What one thinks is social suicide]

43:57.739 --> 43:59.380
[might be seen as adorable by the other .]

44:00.420 --> 44:01.420
Have you had dinner?
